oubray","meanings":["English: variant of   Mowbray  ."]},{"name":"Mayberry","meanings":["English: most probably an altered form of   Mowbray  . It is also found as   Maybury  , which has the form of an English habitational name. There is a place near Woking in Surrey so called; however, this is not recorded until 1885 and is probably derived from the surname. In England this surname is found mainly in the West Midlands; it has also spread into Wales. In Ireland this form is common in Ulster; MacLysaght records that it was taken there from England in the 17th century."]},{"name":"Memory","meanings":["English: variant of   Mowbray  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":31,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":40,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":75,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Mowbray was born about 1184, in Stokesley, Yorkshire, England. She had at least 1 son with William Albini de Mowbray."},"et":{"about 1184–":"umbes 1184–Surnud","1180–1234":"1180–1234","1210–1252":"1210–1252","1184–Female":"1184–Surnud","about 1184":"umbes 1184","aproximadamente 1210":"umbes 1210","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1252":"1252","1184":"1184","1180":"1180","Stokesley, Yorkshire, England":"Stokesley, Yorkshire, England","Easby, Yorkshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Easby, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1184–":"noin 1184–Kuollut","1180–1234":"1180–1234","1210–1252":"1210–1252","1184–Female":"1184–Kuollut","about 1184":"noin 1184","aproximadamente 1210":"noin 1210","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1252":"1252","1184":"1184","1180":"1180","Stokesley, Yorkshire, England":"Stokesley, Yorkshire, England","Easby, Yorkshire, Inglaterra, Reino Unido":"Easby, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1184–":"environ 1184–Décédée","1180–1234":"1180–1234","1210–1252":"1210–1252","1184–Female":"1184–Décédée","about 1184":"environ 1184","aproximadamente 1210":"environ 1210","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1252":"1252","1184":"1184","1180":"1180","Stokesley, Yorkshire, England":"Stokesle